<TITLE> Fakhruddin hands over National Sports Awards </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 21 (bdnews24.com)  Nine sportspersons and an organiser received the National Sports Awards-2006 at a ceremony in Osmani Auditorium Thursday. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed handed each of the awardees Tk. 20,000 cash, a gold medal and a citation. "At times the sports arena and the sports organisations have been politically influenced, which was not desirable," Fakhruddin said. "We want to ensure involvement of athletes and sports lovers in the arena. We want to put competent and responsible people to have a healthy, nice and powerful environment in the sporting community. "We want to restore the rightful democracy by wiping out all corruption and anomalies," he said in his speech. Sports adviser Tapan Chowdhury and sports secretary Mohammed Golam Mustofa Talukdar also attended the ceremony. The awardees are Hasanuzzaman Bablu, Khandakar Wasim Iqbal (football), Mohammed Rafiq (cricket), Sharmin Akhtar (shooting), Ehtesham Sultan (hockey), Fauzia Huda Jui (athletics), Mahmuda Sharif (swimming), Azad Abul Kalam (body building and weightlifting), Nayna Chowdury (judo) and retired lieutenant colonel MA Hamid (organiser). bdn
